    "For the 3rd session, the Shapiro-Wilk test showed no significant deviation from normality across all profiles (all p values > 0.08).",
    "Levene's test indicated homogeneity of variances (all p values > 0.12).",
    "Regarding one-way ANOVA results, there was a significant difference in post-test scores across the different AI interaction profiles, F (4, 135) = 2.98, p =.021.",
    "The effect size was large, η²= 0.81.",
    "However, the Tukey HSD post hoc test did not identify any specific pairs of groups with significant differences."
